svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bqi1665702975044.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bqi1665702975044.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bqi1665702975044.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bqi1665702975044\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      bom\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Connector option that determines whether a Byte Order Mark (BOM) is required in Unicode files accessed by the TXT connector. The behavior for a specific entity can be specified using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/bom</span> switch in an entity-to-connector assignment.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__topic_d61763e1_d61764e1_d61765e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__p_d61766e1_d61767e1_d61768e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$TXT_PARAMS</span>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">bom</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">yes</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">no</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">require</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__p_d61769e1_d61770e1_d61771e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">[ENTITIES]</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$TXT:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/bom</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">yes</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">no</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">require</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__section_qq2_t5h_kcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d851517e113\">Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__table_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__table_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1__entry__1\">Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__table_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1__entry__2\">Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bqi1665702975044__table_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">yes</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bqi1665702975044__table_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1__entry__2\">The connector writes a BOM but allows Unicode\n                        files with or without the BOM. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bqi1665702975044__table_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">no</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bqi1665702975044__table_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1__entry__2\">The connector does not write a BOM but allows\n                        Unicode files with or without the BOM. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bqi1665702975044__table_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">require</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">req</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bqi1665702975044__table_d5423e1_d5424e1_d5425e1__entry__2\">The connector writes a BOM and requires Unicode\n                        files to contain a BOM. This is the default. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__section_b35_55h_kcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d851517e187\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__p_d61778e1_d61779e1_d61780e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">bom</span> connector option only has\n            an effect for Unicode files.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__p_d61781e1_d61782e1_d61783e1\">By default, the TXT connector writes and expects a\n            Byte Order Mark (BOM) in any Unicode file. This is when one or more of the following\n            conditions are met:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__ul_evr_v5h_kcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__li_d27122e1_d27123e1_d27124e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">uni</span> connector option is\n               used. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__li_d27125e1_d27126e1_d27127e1\">The $DEF_CHARSET is <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF8</code>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__li_d27128e1_d27129e1_d27130e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/uni</span> switch is used on a\n               particular file. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__p_d61784e1_d61785e1_d61786e1\">The absence of a BOM results in an error, which can be\n            a problem in some circumstances, such as when:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__ul_gvr_v5h_kcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__li_d27131e1_d27132e1_d27133e1\">The TXT 2.0 connector is used to access files\n               created with the TXT 1.0 connector. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__li_d27134e1_d27135e1_d27136e1\">Third-party applications that do not recognize or\n               provide a BOM may also read and write the files. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__p_d61787e1_d61788e1_d61789e1\">In this case, you can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">bom</span>\n            connector option to make BOM handling more flexible.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__section_zrg_w5h_kcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d851517e242\">/bom</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bqi1665702975044__p_d61793e1_d61794e1_d61795e1\">The BOM handling for a specific entity can be\n            specified using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/bom</span> switch in an entity-to-connector assignment.\n            If the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/bom</span> switch is used, it overrides the value specified by the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">bom</span> connector option in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$TXT_PARAMS</span>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526186\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526186\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "bom Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 bom Connector option that determines whether a Byte Order Mark (BOM) is required in Unicode files accessed by the TXT connector. The behavior for a specific entity can be specified using the /bom switch in an entity-to-connector assignment. [DRIVER_SETTINGS USYS$TXT_PARAMS bom = yes | no | require [ENTITIES] Entity $TXT: FileName /bom = yes | no | require Values Value Meaning yes The connector writes a BOM but allows Unicode files with or without the BOM. no The connector does not write a BOM but allows Unicode files with or without the BOM. require | req The connector writes a BOM and requires Unicode files to contain a BOM. This is the default. Description The bom connector option only has an effect for Unicode files. By default, the TXT connector writes and expects a Byte Order Mark (BOM) in any Unicode file. This is when one or more of the following conditions are met: The uni connector option is used. The $DEF_CHARSET is UTF8 . The /uni switch is used on a particular file. The absence of a BOM results in an error, which can be a problem in some circumstances, such as when: The TXT 2.0 connector is used to access files created with the TXT 1.0 connector. Third-party applications that do not recognize or provide a BOM may also read and write the files. In this case, you can use the bom connector option to make BOM handling more flexible. /bom The BOM handling for a specific entity can be specified using the /bom switch in an entity-to-connector assignment. If the /bom switch is used, it overrides the value specified by the bom connector option in USYS$TXT_PARAMS . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}